CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 13, 1954, pg. 12 reads: " Hill City Contestants For Queen - Among the organizations sponsoring some of these lovely young teenagers, who are striving to wear the Hill City Queen's crown at the may Coronation Ball, are Alpha Alpha Omega Chapter of AKA, Omicron Psi Chapter of Omega Fraternity, Hill City Women's Auxiliary, and Schenley Heights Neighborhood Club. In this group are, left to right...Patricia White...-Harris Photos."Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 8, 1954, pg. 12 reads: "Who Will Be Crowned Teen-Queen Friday Night?  Gloria Bey Still in Lead With 1,707 Votes - Patricia White"
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Patricia White wearing light colored short sleeved blouse with ruffles on collar and down front, posed in front of light colored background in Harris Studio for Hill City Teen Queen contest
